IMAGE_RESIZE_TYPE_ID.description: Sets the type of resize so api can switch between types to compensate the lacking read on api functionality Values: {CROP_FR} - Control the crop settings on the full resolution pipe. {CROP_DS} - Control the crop settings on the downscaler pipe. {SCALER} - Control the width and height of the output of the downscaler. Example: To set the DS crop type set value = CROP_FR. Default Value: CROP

IMAGE_RESIZE_ENABLE_ID.description: Enables or run corresponding crop or downscaler. Values: {RUN} - Apply all changes for sizes and offsets and enable module {DONE} - Done applying changes Default Value: {DONE}

IMAGE_RESIZE_WIDTH_ID.description: Set the width of the system for crop or downscaler. Example: To set width for DS downscaler select DS downscaler and set value = width.

IMAGE_RESIZE_HEIGHT_ID.description: Set the height of the system selected by IMAGE_CROP_AND_DS_SELECT. Example: To set height for DS downscaler select DS downscaler and set value = height.

IMAGE_CROP_YOFFSET_ID.description: Set the y-offset of the system selected by IMAGE_CROP_AND_DS_SELECT. Example: To set y-offset crop and set value = offset.

AF_LENS_STATUS.description: Sets the mode of operation for the AF algorithm. Values: {LENS_SUCCESS} {LENS_FAILED} Default Value: {LENS_FAILED}

AF_MODE_ID.description: Sets the mode of operation for the AF algorithm. Values: {AF_AUTO_SINGLE} {AF_AUTO_CONTINUOUS} {AF_MANUAL} {AF_CALIBRATION} Default Value: {AF_AUTO_SINGLE}

AF_RANGE_LOW_ID.description: Sets the lowest value that the AF algorithm can select. Values: [0-256] Key: 0 - macro mechanical end 256 - infinity end Default Value: AF_RANGE_LOW = 0 AF_RANGE_HIGH = 256

AF_RANGE_HIGH_ID.description: Sets the highest value that the AF algorithm can select. Values: [0-256] Key: 0 - macro mechanical end 256 - infinity end Default Value: AF_RANGE_LOW = 0 AF_RANGE_HIGH = 256

AF_ROI_ID.description: Select which zones are used to gather AF statistics. The region of interest is defined as a rectangle with top-left coordinates (AF_ROI_X1, AF_ROI_Y1) and bottom-right coordinates (AF_ROI_X2, AF_ROI_Y2), with (0,0) defined as the top-left of the image and (255,255) as the bottom right of the image. Values: Four 8 bit numbers concatenated into the 32 bit value. Format: AF_ROI_X1 [31:24] AF_ROI_Y1 [23:16] AF_ROI_X2 [15:8] AF_ROI_Y2 [7:0] Default Values: AF_ROI_X1 = 63 AF_ROI_Y1 = 63 AF_ROI_X2 = 191 AF_ROI_Y2 = 191

AF_MANUAL_CONTROL_ID.description: Manually set the focal length, only available when AF_MODE_ID is set to AF_MANUAL. Values: [0-255] Key: 0 - macro mechanical end 255 - infinity end

AE_MODE_ID.description: Set the AE mode Values: {AE_AUTO} {AE_FULL_MANUAL} {AE_MANUAL_GAIN} {AE_MANUAL_EXPOSURE_TIME} Default Value: {AE_AUTO}

AE_SPLIT_PRESET_ID.description: Set the AE preset Values: {AE_SPLIT_BALANCED} {AE_SPLIT_INTEGRATION_PRIORITY} Default Value: {AE_SPLIT_BALANCED}

AE_GAIN_ID.description: Control the total gain: (Analogue gain)*(Sensor digital gain)*(ISP digital gain). NOTE: Only gains of 1.0 or above are supported. Returns total gain Setting gain is only available when AE_MODE is set to AE_FULL_MANUAL or AE_MANUAL_GAIN Values: Unsigned 16 bit fixed point value (8.8) Format: Integer Part - [15:8] Fractional Part - [7:0] Example: To set a gain of 2.25, the integer part is set to 2 and the fractional part to 64 (0.25*256). The value 576 ((2 << 8) + 64) is then passed to AE_GAIN

AE_EXPOSURE_ID.description: Returns exposure in micro sec. Setting exposure is only available when AE_MODE is set to AE_FULL_MANUAL or AE_MANUAL_EXPOSURE_TIME Values: Unsigned 32 bit value

AE_ROI_ID.description: Select which zones are used to gather AE statistics. The region of interest is defined as a rectangle with top-left coordinates (AE_ROI_X1, AE_ROI_Y1) and bottom-right coordinates (AE_ROI_X2, AE_ROI_Y2), with (0,0) defined as the top-left of the image and (255,255) as the bottom right of the image. Values: Four 8 bit values concatenated into one 32 bit value. Format: AE_ROI_X1 [31:24] AE_ROI_Y1 [23:16] AE_ROI_X2 [15:8] AE_ROI_Y2 [7:0] Default Values: AE_ROI_X1 = 0 AE_ROI_Y1 = 0 AE_ROI_X2 = 255 AE_ROI_Y2 = 255

AE_COMPENSATION_ID.description: Adjust AE compensation to under/over-expose an image Values: Unsigned 8 bit value Description: A value of 128 is no compensation. Values below 128 are negative, Values above 128 are positive. A step of 4 corresponds to 0.5 dB gain. Example: For +1.5 dB compensation the value should be 140 (128+12). For -1.5 dB compensation the value should be 116 (128-12). Default Value: 128

AWB_MODE_ID.description: Select an AWB mode Values: {AWB_AUTO} {AWB_MANUAL} {AWB_DAY_LIGHT} {AWB_CLOUDY} {AWB_INCANDESCENT} {AWB_FLOURESCENT} {AWB_TWILIGHT} {AWB_SHADE} {AWB_WARM_FLOURESCENT} Default Value: {AWB_AUTO}

AWB_TEMPERATURE_ID.description: Returns the current color temperature being used by the AWB algorithm, in kelvin [K], divided by 100. Values: [0-255]

ANTIFLICKER_MODE_ID.description: Set the frequency for the anti-flicker to remove. (0 - disabled) Default Value: 50HZ

FW_REVISION.description: Get fw revision GET returns fw revision number

REGISTERS_SIZE_ID.description: Set/get the size of the register in bits. Values: 8 16 32

REGISTERS_VALUE_ID.description: Set/get the register value. Example: To read an 8bit register at address 0x3c from the sensor set - SET REGISTERS_ADDRESS_ID to 0x3c - SET REGISTERS_SIZE_ID to 8 - SET REGISTERS_SOURCE_ID to SENSOR - GET REGISTERS_VALUE_ID To set a 32bit lens register at address 0x1d to be 0x3f0E2B03: - SET REGISTERS_ADDRESS_ID to 0x1d - SET REGISTERS_SIZE_ID to 32 - SET REGISTERS_SOURCE_ID to LENS - SET REGISTERS_VALUE_ID to 0x3f0E2B03
